    723 CHAPTER 14 Practical Image Superelements Main Index Monitor Point Results in External Superelements Introduction This enhancement allows the user to specify monitor point Bulk Data entries in the external superelement creation run and then recover the monitor point results in the assembly run. The monitor point entries that may be processed in the creation run include MONDSP1, MONPNT1, MONPNT2, MONPNT3, MONSUM, MONSUMT , and MONSUM1. Their results may be recovered in the assembly run for SOLs 101, 103, 108, 109, 111, 112, 200, and 400. Monitor points allow for the calculation of certain key responses and combinations of like responses to be output in a static or dynamic analysis: Summation of applied and inertia-based loads about a point (MONPNT1) Single entity element stress/strain/force output (MONPNT2) Summation of free body interface loads (MONPNT3) Averaged displacement from a collection of grid points (MONDSP1) Benefits This enhancement combines two very popular features in Nastran: external superelements and monitor points. For example, it allows a “subcontractor” to define monitor points within an external superelement and then request the “general contractor” to compute their responses in the assembly run. User Interface There is no new user interface required to access this feature. In the external superelement creation run the user specifies the existing MONITOR and EXTSEOUT Case Control commands along with the following Bulk Data entries: MONDSP1, MONPNT1, MONPNT2, MONPNT3, MONSUM, MONSUMT, and MONSUM1. Then in the assembly run, the user only needs to specify the MONITOR command to obtain the monitor point results in the assembly run. Example Cylinder A simple cylinder 10 units long comprises the external superelement 55. The boundary grids form the residual structure and are located at every 2.5 units along centerline and connected by rigid element “spiders” at 0.0, 2.5, 5.0, 7.5, 10.0 units. The following example is taken from tpl\extse_monpnt\cyl103- op2.dat for the creation run and tpl\extse_monpnt\cyl103-op2r.dat for the assembly run.
